liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Well that last over had enough in it to keep us talking, and it was a fitting end to a remarkable session. A bonkers start with the bat, and then some properly good bowling. Pat Cummins's yorker to Ollie Pope, the loss of Joe Root and Harry Brook despite looking completely impervious to the Aussie attack for so much of their innings, then Ben Stokes coming out and defending everything. Plus all the weird reviews in that final o There were 93 runs scored in the first hour and a bit today, and then 34 scored after drinks. I assume Stokes and Jonny Bairstow will launch after the break, but once again we head to the break with the match in a really interesting spot.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: LUNCH: 5-155 (Stokes 13, Bairstow 1)
